This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with the syntactic patterns of language production. It also involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves the use of neural networks to classify text. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to mimic human language production. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as authorship attribution is a task related to information retrieval. 

Finally, it could also belong to Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as it involves the use of recurrent neural networks.
